        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 6:37PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 637 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 3 miles south of Oologah, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Adair...                          Pryor...
Collinsville...                   Verdigris...
Snowdale State Park...            Locust Grove...
Claremore...                      Spavinaw State Park...
Strang...                         Hoot Owl...
Salina...                         Talala...
Oologah...                        Chouteau...
Pryor Creek...                    Sportsmen Acres Community...
Murphy...                         Spavinaw...
Foyil...                          Bushyhead...

This includes Interstate 44 between mile markers 242 and 268.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
northeastern Oklahoma.</instruction>
